   <concept id="FAR_7_102"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">7.102</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d401e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d415e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						            Agencies shall perform acquisition planning and conduct market research (see <xref href="Part_10.dita#FAR_Part_10"
                        base="i1114815"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  10</xref>) for all acquisitions in order to promote and provide for-</p>
               <ol id="d401e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d415e19" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                Acquisition of commercial items or, to the extent that commercial items suitable to meet the agency’s needs are not available, nondevelopmental items, to the maximum extent practicable (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2377</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3307</xref>); and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d415e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                Full and open competition (see <xref href="Part_6.dita#FAR_Part_6"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>) or, when full and open competition is not required in accordance with <xref href="Part_6.dita#FAR_Part_6"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>, to obtain competition to the maximum extent practicable, with due regard to the nature of the supplies or services to be acquired (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305(a)(1)(A)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3306a)(1)</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d415e47" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
								                Selection of appropriate contract type in accordance with <xref href="Part_16.dita#FAR_Part_16"
                              base="i1105247"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  16</xref>; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d415e55" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
								                Appropriate consideration of the use of pre-existing contracts, including interagency and intra-agency contracts, to fulfill the requirement, before awarding new contracts. (See <xref href="8.002.dita#FAR_8_002"
                              base="i1118176"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.002</xref> through <xref href="8.004.dita#FAR_8_004"
                              base="i1118226"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.004</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_17.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_17_5"
                              base="i1102787"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  17.5</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d415e69" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
						            This planning shall integrate the efforts of all personnel responsible for significant aspects of the acquisition. The purpose of this planning is to ensure that the Government meets its needs in the most effective, economical, and timely manner. Agencies that have a detailed acquisition planning system in place that generally meets the requirements of <xref href="7.104.dita#FAR_7_104"
                        base="i1118917"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.104</xref> and <xref href="7.105.dita#FAR_7_105"
                        base="i1118935"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.105</xref> need not revise their system to specifically meet all of these requirements.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
